						               													<description>Malkyrs: Arenas of Eternity is a collectible card game, with elements of role-playing and timing allowed by the use of computers/phones and wireless technology.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each card contains a RFID chip, which is recognized either by a proprietary reader or a smartphone app, and allows it to keep track of:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     its current Health, Might, Intelligence and Strength levels;&amp;#10;     its learned Skills;&amp;#10;     its Evolutions (by using &amp;quot;Favor&amp;quot; points);&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;which implies that two physically identical cards can be different in-game depending on their playing history.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game itself focuses on a main Champion card, which embodies the player as it casts Action cards to bring its oppenent's Health total to 0.&amp;#10;Playing these Actions has an element of timing, as a computer app keeps tracks of player turns, which by default last 30 seconds; some effects can alter this total, or some cards have different effects depending on how soon/late they have been cast.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each victory grants Glory points, which are tracked by the app, and can be reinvested as Favor points to upgrade cards (see above). The app also allows to play online.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
